# {{name}}

Scaffolded `kind: graphics` cartridge. Edit `cartridge.yaml` and the files
under `shaders/` to define a real rendering pipeline. Defaults target
WebGL 2 + GLSL ES 3.00 because that pair runs unmodified in any modern
browser without a separate native host.

Slug: `{{slug}}`
Trust: `{{trust}}`

## Research grounding

This template is grounded in the *Graphics APIs* research series at
[/Research/GFX/](https://tibsfox.com/Research/GFX/) on tibsfox.com:

- [M1 — OpenGL](https://tibsfox.com/Research/GFX/M1-opengl.html) — the
  desktop host API (versions 1.0 → 4.6).
- [M2 — GLSL](https://tibsfox.com/Research/GFX/M2-glsl.html) — shader
  language, six programmable stages, compile-link model.
- [M3 — WebGL](https://tibsfox.com/Research/GFX/M3-webgl.html) — the
  browser-embedded API and its security model (matches this template's
  default).
- [M4 — Vulkan](https://tibsfox.com/Research/GFX/M4-vulkan.html) —
  explicit-synchronisation API, validation layers, SPIR-V consumption.
- [M5 — Pipeline](https://tibsfox.com/Research/GFX/M5-pipeline.html) —
  the cross-API pipeline: SPIR-V bridge, SPIRV-Cross, ANGLE, MoltenVK.

## Per-API variant recipes

To switch this cartridge to another Khronos API, edit the `chipsets[0]`
block in `cartridge.yaml`:

### OpenGL 4.6 / GLSL 4.60 (desktop)

```yaml
api: opengl
api_version: "4.6"
shader_language: glsl
shader_language_version: "4.60"
host:
  kind: native-c   # or native-rust
  entry: src/main.c
```

### Vulkan 1.4 / SPIR-V (explicit sync, validation layers)

```yaml
api: vulkan
api_version: "1.4"
shader_language: spirv
shader_language_version: "1.6"
runtime:
  validation_layers: true
toolchain:
  glslang: true        # compile GLSL → SPIR-V
  spirv_cross: true    # cross-compile SPIR-V → backend shader
host:
  kind: native-c
```

### OpenGL ES 3.2 (mobile)

```yaml
api: opengl-es
api_version: "3.2"
shader_language: glsl-es
shader_language_version: "3.20"
host:
  kind: native-c
```

## How to run

### 1. Validate the cartridge shape

```
skill-creator cartridge validate ./cartridge.yaml
```

Exit code `0` + `valid: true` confirms the schema + cross-chipset checks
pass.

### 2. Run the eval gates

```
skill-creator cartridge eval ./cartridge.yaml
```

Graphics cartridges are gated by `all_graphics_sources_declare_stage`:
every entry in `sources[].stage` must be listed in the top-level
`shader_stages[]` array.

### 3. Preview in a browser (WebGL default)

```
npx vite
```

The scaffolded `host.kind: vite` points at `index.html`, which loads the
two shader files via `fetch()` and compiles them into a WebGL 2 program.
Any modern browser with WebGL 2 support (Chrome 56+, Firefox 51+,
Safari 15+) will render the result.

### 4. Native hosts (OpenGL, Vulkan)

`host.kind: native-c` / `native-rust` / `mcp` are declared here for
forward compatibility but the runtime shells are not yet shipped with
gsd-skill-creator. For now, native cartridges are shape-validated only;
bring your own host (GLFW, SDL2, Vulkan-Hpp, etc.) and point it at the
shader paths declared in `sources[]`.

## Load + validate

```
skill-creator cartridge load ./cartridge.yaml
skill-creator cartridge validate ./cartridge.yaml
skill-creator cartridge eval ./cartridge.yaml
```
